race.comment: Keen on the unbeaten BIANCELLI (9) to round out the day. She's a sharp mare who won well with 60kg at her only run last preparation having looked good in two soft wins the campaign prior. She's off a similar break here and maps to either lead or take the trail from the ideal gate. Tipping she goes close again. CODIGO (3) has just found one better at both runs this time in, trying hard at Flemington over 1100m last time out. Back to 1000m looks okay although there is a lot of pressure drawn inside her. CELERITY (13) is interesting, first up and now with Ciaron Maher. She's a sharp sort with pieces of strong form and can be darting through late. GIN A TONIC (1) won over the 955m at Moonee Valley fresh and has to be respected from a good draw. HARRY GOT STYLES (4) is 2/2 over this route and finds the right race to be competitive.
